I&#39;ve just been poking around in the NEAT code that goes with HyperNEAT,
and have found something I don&#39;t understand. In the file
NEAT_GeneticPopulation.cpp, around lines 350 -380 is the code:

   if (!species-&gt;isReproduced())
   {
     species-&gt;setReproduced(true);
     if (ind-&gt;getFitness() &gt; species-&gt;getBestIndividual()-&gt;getFitness())
     { species-&gt;setBestIndividual(ind);
       //&lt;&lt;&lt;
     }
     if ((a==0&&forceCopyGenerationChampion)||...
     {  ...
        species-&gt;decrementOffspringCount();
     }
     if (a==0)   //****
     {
        species-&gt;updateAgeOfLastImprovement();
     }
    }
// Some code removed for clarity

Looking at the line //****, as I see it, The species age of last
last improvement, can get set even when the species hasn&#39;t improved.
I would have expected this snippet of code to be at the position marked
with //&lt;&lt;&lt;, to guarantee it only gets updated when there is an true
improvement, or have I missed something (the usual case).

